\par\plain {\f2\fs28\b0\i0 In software development there are several monospaced fonts that support ligature symbols such as Cascadia Code, Fira Code (a modification of Fira Mono) and JetBrains Mono. Most programming languages rely on certain sequences of symbols as part of the syntax such as \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8220\'93}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0 !=}{\f2\fs28\b0\i0 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8221\'94, \u8220\'93}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0 ==}{\f2\fs28\b0\i0 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8221\'94 and \u8220\'93}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0 ++}{\f2\fs28\b0\i0 \loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8221\'94.}
